name: How can I tell if Iâ€™m experiencing burnout?

speech:
Emotional Signs:

Feeling exhausted and depleted, even after resting
Feeling cynical, detached, or negative about your work or life
Reduced sense of accomplishment or satisfaction
Increased irritability, frustration, or anger
Anxiety, depression, or difficulty sleeping

Physical Signs:

Headaches, muscle tension, or stomachaches
Changes in appetite or sleep patterns
Fatigue or lack of energy
Frequent illness or weakened immune system

Behavioral Signs:

Withdrawing from social activities or hobbies
Procrastinating or avoiding work responsibilities
Increased use of alcohol, drugs, or other unhealthy coping mechanisms
Difficulty concentrating or making decisions
Difficulty relaxing or enjoying activities you once did
